programme.desc: Steve Backshall heads for India, where he goes on the trail of the saw-scaled viper. He also gets too close to the razor-sharp claws of the sloth bear

programme.title: Top Gear
programme.desc: Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond and James May attempt to improve the ambulance, with the presenters all going their own separate ways to enhance one area they think could do with an overhaul. James focuses on passenger comfort, Richard tries to shorten response times by getting other drivers out of the way more effectively, an issue Jeremy tackles with the invention of what he calls the 'sports ambulance'. Their three very different creations are then put to the test with a series of severe and often messy challenges. Plus, Formula One driver Daniel Ricciardo is the Star in the Reasonably Priced Car

programme.title: Guy Montgomery's Guy Mont-Spelling Bee Australia
programme.desc: Aaron Chen joins Guy to test the spelling prowess of Australia's favourite personalities with wild spelling challenges to befuddle, bamboozle and bedazzle them. This episode sees comedians Urzila Carlson, Nazeem Hussain, Danielle Walker and Tom Gleeson compete

programme.title: Guy Montgomery's Guy Mont-Spelling Bee Australia
programme.desc: Co-host Aaron Chen joins Guy to test the spelling prowess of comedians Geraldine Hickey, Pete Helliar, Urvi Majumdar and Nazeem Hussein

programme.title: The Traitors Ireland
programme.desc: Tensions are high as suspicion is everywhere. An explosive argument leaves the players reeling, and threatens to have an impact on the round table. Presented by Siobhn McSweeney

programme.title: The Traitors Ireland
programme.desc: As the game intensifies at Slane Castle, a shocking turn of events leaves the players unsure of who to believe. Presented by Siobhn McSweeney

programme.title: Sin City: The Real Las Vegas
programme.desc: Part one of two. Tir Dhondy reveals the realities behind modern Las Vegas. The first episode explores the risk of crime faced by tourists and visits a pool party where massive screens show scores of live sports events from around the world so that partygoers can bet from the comfort of their sun lounger

programme.title: Sin City: The Real Las Vegas
programme.desc: Part two of two. Tir Dhondy goes further into the underbelly of Las Vegas to investigate how the reinvention of the city to pull in a new generation of visitors is affecting locals

programme.title: Top Gear: Top Gear Winter Olympics Special
programme.sub-title: Top Gear Winter Olympics Special Season 7, Episode 7
programme.desc: Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond and James May head to Norway to find out how a selection of cars fare when taking part in Winter Olympic events. Their experiments include firing a rocket-powered Mini off a ski jump, tackling the biathlon with 4x4s, staging a game of motorised ice hockey and timing the Jaguar XK in a speed-skating race

programme.title: The Beauty Queen and the Catfish: The Mystery Medic
programme.desc: The story of Kilmarnock nurse Adele Rennie, who pretended to be handsome, professional men to target, harass, stalk and exploit hundreds of women. When Dr David Graham starts flirting with former beauty queen Abbie Draper online, she turns sleuth and uncovers a trail of deception, crazy coincidences and stories that just don't add up

programme.title: Long Story Short: Beyond
programme.desc: A shy 17-year-old outsider is marked for abduction as part of his new home town's terrifying tradition. He must evade capture and make it through the night, navigating love, friendship and events that are beyond explanation

programme.title: Doctor Who: Night Terrors
programme.desc: A child's bedroom is turned into the scariest place in the universe when his cupboard becomes home to every kind of fear imaginable. His parents remain baffled by the problem, so the boy makes a desperate bid for help. When his cries manage to break the barriers of time and space, the Doctor decides to make a house call. Sci-fi adventure, guest starring Daniel Mays, with Matt Smith, Karen Gillan and Arthur Darvill

programme.title: Doctor Who: The Girl Who Waited
programme.sub-title: The Girl Who Waited Season 6, Episode 10
programme.desc: Amy is trapped in a quarantine facility for victims of an alien plague. With the Time Lord unable to survive the disease, it is up to Rory to break in and rescue her, but he discovers that time moves differently in the facility, and Amy has been trapped there for years. Matt Smith and Karen Gillan star in the sci-fi adventure, with the voice of Imelda Staunton

programme.title: Gavin & Stacey
programme.desc: The newlyweds return from their honeymoon to a big welcome from both their families. However, Smithy seems disconcerted by his pal's return and Nessa makes a confession that spoils the happy occasion. Comedy, starring Mathew Horne, James Corden and Joanna Page

programme.title: Gavin & Stacey
programme.desc: Smithy goes missing following Nessa's shocking revelation, and the boys try to track him down to persuade him to accept his responsibilities. Meanwhile, Stacey is forced to contemplate the consequences of transforming her long-distance relationship with Gavin into a functioning marriage

programme.title: Mrs Brown's Boys: Mammy's Ass
programme.desc: Doting mother Agnes resolves to have a proper family Christmas to celebrate son Trevor taking a break from missionary work for the first time in years. But Dermot is under pressure to spend the holiday with his posh in-laws, neighbour Winnie needs help finding a job, Buster has problems delivering the turkey, and to top it all off, there is no sign of any snow. Written by and starring Brendan O'Carroll

programme.title: Dinosaur
programme.desc: After eight months working on the dig on the Isle of Wight, Nina is desperate to get back to her home comforts - as well as to see if she and Lee can pick things up where they left them. But all her plans are thrown into disarray when her boss Dr Dunne offers her an opportunity. Sitcom, starring Ashley Storrie

programme.title: Dinosaur
programme.desc: Nina hopes life will return to normal back in Glasgow, but a surprise arrival at the museum and a revelation about Bo means things are going to be far from straightforward

programme.title: Only Child: Eh?
programme.desc: Bit-part actor and only child Richard travels back from London to his family home in the Highlands to visit his elderly father Ken a year on from the passing of his mum. However, he soon realises his dad might be in need of a bit more full-time help, not that eccentric, strong-willed technophobe Ken would agree. Comedy, starring Gregor Fisher and Greg McHugh

programme.title: Only Child: Raisins
programme.desc: Richard decides the time has come to declutter his father's house of all his junk, but Ken has suspicions over his son's true motives. The arrival of local handyman Mr Oddjob, Richard's former school adversary Craig, complicates matters further as chaos commences. Comedy, starring Gregor Fisher and Greg McHugh

programme.title: Daddy Issues: Happy Tears
programme.desc: When hedonistic 24-year-old Gemma discovers she is pregnant after a one-night stand, she has no choice but to turn to her hapless father, Malcolm, for support. A sweet-but-lost man in a domestic crisis, he must learn to rebuild his relationship with his daughter, though they soon find living together will prove difficult. Sitcom, starring Aimee Lou Wood and David Morrissey

programme.title: The Vintage French Farmhouse
programme.desc: Antiques dealers Ian Humphries, Viki Knott and Moses Otunla head to Occitanie to visit Le Grand Dballage (The Big Unpacking) in Pzenas, a twice-yearly held market where more than 100 traders take to the streets. It's a rare opportunity to pick up two interesting objects each to sell for a profit online, in just a day. Mid-century maestro Moses opts for a coffee table with an artistically-tiled top. Ian goes for something much more unique - an early rustic dynamite cart. However, given its fragile state, the wheels might come off this purchase before he even gets it in the van

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Cameraman Charlie Hamilton James heads to the Peruvian jungle to chart the hazardous life of a giant otter and its unruly family of six cubs. The young ones must learn how to swim, catch piranha and avoid predators, with Charlie managing to capture a fight between the otters and a caiman, a large aquatic reptile closely related to the alligator and the crocodile

programme.title: Flog It!: Essex 58

programme.title: Winter Olympics 2026: 2026 Day One - 1
programme.desc: Hazel Irvine presents live coverage of day one of the 25th staging of the Games, with events coming from Milan and Cortina d'Ampezzo in Italy. Great Britain continue their quest for glory in the curling mixed doubles when they face Canada in a round-robin match at Cortina Curling Olympic Stadium. The men's downhill takes place at Stelvio Ski Centre, with Switzerland's back-to-back World Cup champion Marco Odermatt heading a strong Swiss team, and 36-year-old Dominik Paris carrying the hopes of the home nation. In cross-country skiing, the women's 10km+10km skiathlon gets under way at Tesero Cross-Country Skiing Stadium

programme.title: Winter Olympics 2026: 2026 Day One - 2
programme.desc: Jeanette Kwakye presents further live coverage of day one of the 25th staging of the Games, as more medals are decided in Milan and Cortina d'Ampezzo in Italy. Team GB's mixed doubles curling team of Bruce Mouat and Jennifer Dodds face the USA's 2023 world champions Korey Dropkin and Cory Thiesse in their latest round robin match at Cortina Curling Olympic Stadium. Elsewhere, the women's 3,000m speed skating event takes place at Milano Speed Skating Stadium, with sensation Irene Schouten of the Netherlands, who won three gold medals at the 2022 Games, expected to be in contention. Plus, Sweden face Italy and USA take on Finland in the women's ice hockey at Milano Santagiulia Ice Hockey Arena and Milano Rho Ice Hockey Arena respectively

programme.title: Winter Olympics 2026: 2026 Day One - 3
programme.desc: Clare Balding presents the concluding live coverage of day one of the 25th staging of the Games, featuring all the key events in Italy. In the luge, the second and final run of the men's singles discipline takes place at Cortina Sliding Centre, while over at Predazzo Ski Jumping Stadium, medals are awarded in the women's individual event. The third and concluding men's snowboarding big air run also takes place at Livigno Snow Park, an event which China's Su Yiming delighted the Beijing crowd with victory in four years ago. Plus, Canada begin their defence of their women's ice hockey title when they face Switzerland at Milano Rho Ice Hockey Arena

programme.title: Rick Astley: Reel Stories
programme.desc: The singer sits down with Dermot O' Leary in a London cinema to talk about his life and career, viewing some of his most famous performances and interviews from over the years. Rick recalls his formative time at Stock, Aitken & Waterman's studios, where he rose from tea-maker to global pop star, and reflects on his complex relationship with fame, his decision to leave SAW, and his subsequent step away from the music business. He discusses the unexpected impact of the viral Rickrolling phenomenon, what ultimately drew him back into recording after two decades away, and the remarkable resurgence of his career

programme.title: Rick Astley at Glastonbury 2023
programme.desc: Clara Amfo and Lauren Laverne introduce the singer's set on the Pyramid Stage, featuring performances of Together Forever, Whenever You Need Somebody and Never Gonna Give You Up as well as covers of Harry Styles' As It Was and AC/DC's Highway to Hell

programme.title: Stock Aitken Waterman at the BBC
programme.desc: Mike Stock, Matt Aitken and Pete Waterman were the producers who conquered the UK charts in the 1980s, with their instantly recognisable brand of disco floor-filling pop hits. They divided the nation between those who loved their high-energy sound and the singers they transformed into cheesy pop sensations, and a music press that loathed them for turning music-making into a production line. This selection celebrates some of their most memorable hits, from acts including Kylie Minogue, Jason Donovan, Rick Astley, Dead or Alive, Donna Summer, Bananarama, and Mel and Kim

programme.desc: Tom assists with interior window trim and custom storm windows. Richard checks out an electric meter and panels. Mark follows work on the hardscape. Kevin watches the assembly of a decorative shed.

programme.desc: Trees and sod are transplanted with Jenn, while a custom deck hatch is installed to access the basement. Inside, Kevin and Jeff assemble a smart lock system and Tom helps mount a unique range hood.

programme.title: This Old House
programme.desc: Work happens in the kitchen. Kevin and Tom tackle the molding. The pantry gets a secret door. Countertops, backsplash and tile are installed. A new wood mantle goes around the gas fireplace.

programme.title: This Old House

programme.desc: The show returns to Dorchester, MA, the home of the first This Old House project, to follow the renovation of a triple decker that burned from illegal fireworks.

programme.desc: Asbestos is removed from exposed ductwork. Richard meets the new plumber. Jenn visits a community garden. A local historian speaks about triple deckers. Tom and Charlie pull off the melted siding.

programme.title: This Old House
programme.desc: The back porches are brought to code. Ice blasting is used to get rid of the fire odor. New vinyl siding gets installed. Homeowner Carol considers new accent colors to match. Framing begins inside.

programme.title: This Old House
programme.desc: Jenn creates a patio building team. Heath rewires a section with intact plaster. Charlie and Tom hang a fire rated door. Richard explains how a tub fits in. Kevin and Tom install a replacement window.

programme.desc: Tom works with new apprentices. Kevin meets them and learns about YouthBuild. Homeowner Carol looks at kitchen cabinets and counters. Richard works with James on separate HVAC systems.

programme.title: This Old House

programme.title: This Old House
programme.desc: Tom and Kevin reinstall cabinets that survived the fire. Tom teaches apprentices to trim a window. HVAC contractor James shows Richard the plan for hot water. Carol and her sister shop for appliances.

programme.title: This Old House
programme.desc: Illegal fireworks caused a fire in the Dorchester triple decker. Charlie Silva along with local contractors put this house back together. After a long wait, Carol and family can now move back home.

programme.desc: The number of people entering the building trades is declining. This Old House launched the Generation Next initiative to encourage young people to consider the trades as a viable profession.

programme.desc: Kevin, Richard, and Tom follow a family on their journey to restore an abandoned house in Detroit. The city has a program to bring these empty houses back to life, revitalizing the neighborhoods.

programme.title: This Old House

programme.desc: A bay window is removed and reframed for a new. An old school is being restored into apartments for veterans. The underside of a deck is the "roof" of living space below. Pipe locations are discussed.
